The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   Business Briefs
                              
	 Mumbai, June 11: Construction company Gammon India has acquired a 50 per cent and a 75.1 per cent stake, respectively, in two Italy- based companies  Sadelmi Spa and Franco Tosi Meccanica Spa  for 47.5 million euros (over Rs 315.85 crore). Through its offshore subsidiaries, the company has acquired shares in Sadelmi and Franco Tosi through additional infusion of equity.                             
	 New Delhi, June 11: ifcis board will meet tomorrow to consider inviting bids for selling a 26 per cent stake. The Ifci board will take a view on the issue of induction of a strategic investor, besides other items.                            
	 New Delhi, June 11: The government has amended the area based excise duty exemptions for units in Jammu amp; Kashmir, the Northeast, Sikkim and Kutch district of Gujarat to allow refund of excise duty based on the value addition made by the units.                             
	 New Delhi, June 11: Indiabulls Properties Investment Trust today closed 10 per cent below its issue price on the Singapore Stock Exchange on its debut day.                            
	 Mumbai, June 11: Arvind Mills has called off its joint venture with Italian apparel maker Diesel BV by mutual consent, with effect from today.                                                                                                                         
